CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 4, 1959, pg. A19, reads: "Dancing Sisters - Diana and Patrice Bolling were the only race participants in the 'Spinning in the Spotlight' dance revue, recently held at the Monongahela High School, Monongahela, Pa. They are the daughters of Mr. and Mrs. John Bolling. Their mother is the former Hazel Davenport of the Davenport Sisters Quartet."
TitMainTitle: Sisters Diana Bolling and Patrice Bolling in tap dancing costumes posed on top of piano for "Spinning in the Spotlight" dance revue at Monongahela High School
